<exercise checkit-seed="0005" checkit-slug="LT4" checkit-title="Continuity">
    <statement>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>Determine the value of <m>b</m> to make <m>g(x)</m> continuous at <m>x=2</m>.</p>
                <p>
                    <me>
                        g(x) = \begin{cases}
                        b + x, &amp; x &lt; 2 \\
                        x^{2} - 6 \, x + 10, &amp; x \geq 2
                        \end{cases}
                    </me>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
Classify the type of discontinuity present at <m>x=4</m> for 
the function <m>h(x)</m>.</p>
                <p>
                    <me>
                        h(x) = \begin{cases}
                        7 \, x - 20, &amp; x &lt; 4 \\
                        2, &amp; x = 4 \\
                        -3 \, x + 20, &amp; x &gt; 4 \\
                        \end{cases}
                    </me>
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <ol>
            <li>To make <m>g(x)</m> continuous at <m>x=2</m>, let <m>b=0</m>.</li>
                <li>
The function <m>h(x)</m> has a
removable discontinuity.
                </li>
        </ol>
    </answer>
</exercise>
